    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Crosses in the shape of a Maltese cross, or occasionally other equal-armed crosses, having the color green. It was the device of the order of hospitalers of St. Lazarus of Jerusalem, which had a special duty of protecting leper hospitals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kruisen in de vorm van een Maltezer kruis (of soms een ander gelijkarmig kruis) met een groene kleur. Het werd gevoerd door de Orde van Sint-Lazarus van Jeruzalem, die was belast met de verdediging van leprahospitalen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>外觀類似馬爾他十字架的綠色十字架，或為其他兩臂等長的十字架造型。耶路撒冷的聖拉撒路醫院騎士團以此種綠色十字架為紋章圖案，此騎士團的特殊職責為護衛痲瘋病院。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
